# No Deletions Without Production Replacement (HARD RULE)

This repo is **production-only**. The assistant must not “delete to make the problem disappear.”

## Absolute rule

- If the assistant **removes** any UI, logic, route, feature, or user-facing behavior, it must be replaced with a **real, functional, production-quality implementation** that preserves the original capability.
- The assistant must **never** delete code as a shortcut to “fix” errors, reduce counts, or silence audits.

## Allowed exceptions (must be explicit)

The assistant may remove something only if:

- The user explicitly approves the removal, **or**
- The assistant proves it is truly unused/dead code **and** documents the evidence (imports/usage search + reasoning) in the PR/commit notes.

## Replacement requirements

When removal is necessary (refactor/cleanup):

- Provide an equivalent implementation (same feature outcome) in the same PR/change-set.
- Keep behavior stable unless the user explicitly requests a behavior change.
- Update tests and docs so the system remains launch-ready.

